nt; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a></p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So if you sell a thing for $100 in cas=
h, you get $100 in cash, but =E2=80=94=C2=A0after the costs and delays asso=
ciated with handling cash and turning it into bank money =E2=80=94=C2=A0tha=
t=E2=80=99s worth less than $100 of bank money. I don=E2=80=99t know how mu=
ch less; it will depend on the particulars of your business. But it=E2=80=
=99s=C2=A0<em>possible=C2=A0</em>that it will be less than $97, and it will=
 be cheaper for you to accept credit cards than cash.</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
